From: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Thu, 19 Sep 2019 22:04:28 +0200
Subject: crypto: chtls - simplify a bit 'create_flowc_wr_skb()'
Patch-mainline: v5.5-rc1
Git-commit: 3dc8b01ebcdd3a43d6c766618b92c2becbcf96b8
References: jsc#SLE-15129

Use '__skb_put_data()' instead of rewritting it.
This improves readability.

Signed-off-by: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Signed-off-by: Herbert Xu <herbert@gondor.apana.org.au>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/crypto/chelsio/chtls/chtls_io.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/crypto/chelsio/chtls/chtls_io.c
+++ b/drivers/crypto/chelsio/chtls/chtls_io.c
@@ -97,7 +97,7 @@ static struct sk_buff *create_flowc_wr_s
 	if (!skb)
 		return NULL;
 
-	memcpy(__skb_put(skb, flowclen), flowc, flowclen);
+	__skb_put_data(skb, flowc, flowclen);
 	skb_set_queue_mapping(skb, (csk->txq_idx << 1) | CPL_PRIORITY_DATA);
 
 	return skb;
